        "Create a comparison table for the four RNA types (mRNA, tRNA, rRNA) plus two regulatory types (snRNA, miRNA) — columns: (1) full name; (2) structure; (3) where made; (4) function in the central dogma; (5) approximate size in nucleotides; (6) relative abundance in cell. Use this table as a self-test by covering columns 3–6 and reconstructing them."
