                "Dissect a broad bean seed after soaking overnight: (1) remove the testa and note its texture and thickness; (2) locate the hilum (seed scar) and micropyle; (3) separate the two cotyledons carefully; (4) with a hand lens, locate and sketch the miniature embryo — identify radicle (root tip), plumule (shoot tip), and epicotyl. Compare the fresh cotyledon thickness with a dry unsoaked seed sliced alongside. Calculate the percentage increase in size after soaking to quantify imbibition.",
